&nbsp;<br />
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Q&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; On financial re-reg, what&rsquo;s the White House going to do to fend off lobbying, to soften or change the impact of the regulations?<br />
&nbsp;<br />
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; MR. GIBBS:&nbsp; Look, obviously there will be an extensive rulemaking procedure in order to fulfill the legislative intent, and I think that -- again, I think we're clear at what provisions mean and what they&rsquo;re trying to prevent and how and what activities should and should not be allowed.&nbsp; Obviously the implementation of this, the additional offices and bureaus that the legislation calls for would be important appointments for the President to consider.<br />
